be in it of a truth,</HI> 1 Cor. xiv. 25.8. Satan &s;ometimes <HI>departed</HI> and left me <HI>for a &s;ea&s;on,</HI> Luke iv. 13 and then I had &s;ome intermi&s;&s;ion of my &s;ore trouble. 9. I found a &s;ecret hope begot and cheri&s;hed, I could not tell how, at &s;ome &s;ea&s;ons, even amid&s;t the violence of temptations, that I &s;hould be &s;atis|fied, <HI>and that I &s;hould yet have good <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="3 letters">&s;e to prai&s;t God,</HI> P&s;al. xlii. 5.8, 11, and that what <HI>I knew not now,</HI> I &s;hould know hereafter, John xiii. 7. which was &s;trength|ened by the con&s;ideration of what others had met with, who had been try&s;ted with temptations that were &s;ome way like mine: Albeit, I doubted, if ever, in all re|&s;pects,
